{"id":"1809.08184","submitter":"Jan-David Hardtke","authors":"Jan-David Hardtke","title":"Higher derivatives of the inverse tangent function and a summation\n  formula involving binomial coefficients","comments":"8 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In 2017, O. Deiser and C. Lasser obtained an explicit formula for the $n$-th\nderivative of the inverse tangent function. We calculate this derivative by a\ndifferent method based on Fa\\`a di Bruno's formula. Comparing the two results\nleads to the following identity for binomial coefficients:\n$$\\sum_{i=m}^{[n/2]}\\frac{(-1)^i}{4^i}\\binom{i}{m}\\binom{n-i}{i}=\\frac{(-1)^m}{2^n}\\binom{n+1}{2m+1},$$\nwhere $n,m\\in \\mathbb{N}_0$ and $m\\leq [n/2]$. As was pointed out to the author\nby C. Krattenthaler, this formula is a special case of Gau\\ss's formula for the\nhypergeometric function $_2F_1$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Sep 2018 16:07:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Oct 2018 16:14:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-22"}
