y interfaces preserved within rock\noutcrops, and finally focusing on finding minerals associated with redox\nreactions and traces of carbon and diagnostic biosignatures. The lessons from\nEarth show that ancient rock hosted life is preserved in the fossil record and\nconfirmable via a suite of morphologic, organic, mineralogical and isotopic\nfingerprints and microscopic textures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Sep 2018 18:40:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-16"}
