n. Although some of the regions with high spatial correlation are\nassociated with HI self-absorption features, suggesting that it is produced by\nthe cold atomic gas, the correlation is not exclusive to this kind of region.\nThe HOG results also indicate significant differences between individual\nregions: some show spatial correlation in channels around $v_{HI}\\approx\nv_{^{13}CO}$ while others present this correlation in velocity channels\nseparated by a few km/s. We associate these velocity offsets to the effect of\nfeedback and to the presence of physical conditions that are not included in\nthe atomic-cloud-collision simulations, such as more general magnetic field\nconfigurations, shear, and global gas infall.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Sep 2018 23:05:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 2 Jan 2019 16:07:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
